athbf{q} + 6\\mathbf{r}}{12} - \\frac{\\mathbf{p} + \\mathbf{r}}{2}$.\n\n## 8: Simplify $\\overrightarrow{ES}$\nSimplifying $\\overrightarrow{ES}$ gives $\\overrightarrow{ES} = \\frac{\\mathbf{p} + 5\\mathbf{q} + 6\\mathbf{r} - 6\\mathbf{p} - 6\\mathbf{r}}{12} = \\frac{-5\\mathbf{p} + 5\\mathbf{q}}{12} = \\frac{5(\\mathbf{q} - \\mathbf{p})}{12}$.\n\n## 9: Calculate the ratio of lengths $\\frac{EF}{ES}$\nThe ratio of the lengths is $\\frac{EF}{ES} = \\frac{|\\overrightarrow{EF}|}{|\\overrightarrow{ES}|} = \\frac{|\\frac{\\mathbf{q} - \\mathbf{p}}{2}|}{|\\frac{5(\\mathbf{q} - \\mathbf{p})}{12}|} = \\frac{|\\mathbf{q} - \\mathbf{p}|}{2} \\cdot \\frac{12}{5|\\mathbf{q} - \\mathbf{p}|}$.\n\n## 10: Simplify the ratio\nThis simplifies to $\\frac{EF}{ES} = \\frac{12}{2 \\cdot 5} = \\frac{6}{5}$.\n\n## 11: Convert the ratio to a numerical value\nThe numerical value of the ratio $\\frac{EF}{ES}$ is $\\frac{6}{5}$ or $1.2$.\n\nThe answer is {"answer": "1.2", "confidence": 90}'
